I feel like perfectionism and depression go hand in hand so this really helps me. It didn’t happen over night. I’ve been dealing with depression for almost 13 years now. It took a lot of time and effort. Do what you can. I promise it’s enough
When I’m depressed my motto is “something is better than nothing”

I found that the shorter and simpler routines are the easier it is for me to do them when I’m depressed. When I’m depressed I’m not going to do my whole body butter and oil routine. I’m just going to put on moisturizer where I can and call it a day.

Also my hair, i found that keeping it parted and in braids really prevents it from matting up. I haven’t had an episode since the end of December🤞🏻. I’m exhausted because I’ve been pushing through but I’m surviving :)

Honestly my eczema has had a huge impact on this because I’ll get a flare up if I go even one day without showering. It’s kind of frustrating because when I’m depressed I truly don’t have the energy to shower but this 10 minute routine gives me a peace of mind when I’m depressed

I only do this 10 min routine when my depression is bad. Most of the time when I’m in the shower I’ll find the energy to do other things like body scrubs eyc but If I don’t have the energy I just do body wash, maybe a sugar scrub on my arms and feet and face wash.

No matter how bad it gets I actually no longer skip showering. I haven’t in nearly a decade. I have a 10 min shower routine so it’s not as exhausting and I do the bare minimum with moisturizer etc. My hair is in braids and is usually fine for a few days with dry shampoo.
